rComments: Avoid at all costs. Ditto to everything the person below says. And you might as well teach yourself the material. He's a nice guy but really hard to follow.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Goes off on tangents. Demotivates students who watch the weboption videos saying they won't pass. Doesn't follow syllabus. Unclear/sometimes contradicts textbook.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Professor Bors is amazing despite what many students might say. Minimum A- marks on PSYB07 and PSYC08 should be required though - you can't follow if you don't already have a solid stats intro and feel passionate about the subject. It does take a few lectures to get used to his thought process but once you get it you see how amazing he is.

He's a brilliant guy - so brilliant that he is sometimes hard to follow. When things in lectures don't make sense, go to your book and your TAs - they can help! If you understand the concepts you'll pass the exams easily.
Great prof, really tries to make the best of a difficult course and difficult material.

worst. professor. ever. uses a bunch of PDFs with just formulas (which many have mistakes in them), talks and talks about how they work, but rarely does math. if you know stats or calculus, you might be fine , but beware! DO NOT TAKE HIS COURSES unless you have to.

He is a good prog. He does seem to off on a tangent but if you listen carefully then it all finally clicks and connects in the end. He knows a lot about the subject so he gives you a lot more than the textbook material to think about.
Goes off on a tangent

Needs to organize his course better. Powerpoint slides with a few formulas each is not working. This is a relatively easy course to teach. Instead he goes on for long hours in unrelated tangents. Also he doesn't do much "MATH" in class. TAs do all the math. His job is to show the formulas and to talk way tooooo much about why they work.

Friendly and approchable prof that's humourous and excited about stats. However, difficult to understand him, tends to tangent off, shows deriving and formulas that are unnessesary.I found the TA's the most helpful. Material is not hard, but he can make is sound difficult. Midterm is very easy. Prepare for a very long final with bell curved marks.
If only someone else taught this course, it would be much easier and there wouldn't be as many complaints as there are. Will never take a course with him again.
Horrible Prof, disorganized lectures. Awful TA's.

At first glance, his lectures are disorganized and may be frasturating. But online lectures made all the difference for me. I NEVER opened the textbook and still got an A-. If you focus on his lectures (esp online), and go over them step by step, its def doable. Final was long, but marks came out fine. All in all, he is knowledgable and approach-e

Very unorganized lectures (overheads? really?). Prof is very excited about stats... which makes him go off on random incomprehensible tangents. The exams were very easy, but overall I came out of the course learning next to nothing about stats. I'm definitely not prepared for C08... unless he is teaching, in which case it probably won't matter.
he is very intelligent. he becomes confusing during lecture. but the course materail is ver easy. read the text and then he will make sense. Do the review questions.The easiest course at utsc.

He is a very intelligent, he knows what he is talking about..he's worked for NASA. In some way, he's too smart to be teaching University students..and I agree that he does talk to us like we know exactly what he is talking about. I didn't pay attention in B07 or C08 but did have a study group...and managed to get A's in both classes. So a study gro
He made a boring topic less  boring and easy to understand.

He's not that bad, so I don't understand what people are talking about.  If you go to lecture and keep up with the work, you'll be fine.  Take it from someone who was absolutely dreading this course in the beginning.
excellent

He's the worst. I had straight As in all of my other courses in the semester that I took this class, but guess what my mark was in statistics? C! He hurt my average and he'll hurt your average too, so watch out!
new prof would make course a lot easier...esp since its mandatory and a lot of students enter the class scared...he doesnt help by talking like we've all studied stats for yrss
he needs to step down and let others teach .. course is very easy ... but he confuses students to the max!!
aight

i didn't even buy the textbook and everything i studied was based on his notes. but his notes were hard to understand. he keeps repeating the same thing over and over in the lectures, very boring, it's hard to hear what he says and i probably skipped most of them. however the midterm and exam were fair, overall a good prof
Good prof, he was fair with his midterms and exam.

Bors is a very good prof!!! i  dont know what everyone is complaining about. he is very knowledgable and approachable and humble and funny! his midterm is basically a freebee...everyone should have killed that!!!! and the final was harder than the mid but not impossible. he is awesome and he cares about our understanding of the material. thumbs up!

All I can say to everyone who whines and complains about this class is psychology is a science.  Science involves math.  Lot's of people who take psyc are not math people, and so complain about this class, but honestly this class was a joke compared to real math classes.  Bors did an awesome job!  He actually challenges you like university should!
Amazing professor.

He explains the subject matter in a way that makes the material much more complicated than it already is.The quizzes are not bad, but the exams are very hard.He does seem interested in wanting to help, he likes to answer questions and encourages students to see him during office hours, but he needs to learn how to explain concepts better.

the subject is BORING, can't do anything about it. Bors tries to explain everything as clearly as possible and is really helpful if you have any questions. if u dont need the course, don't take it. if u do need it, prep urself for hard work

All I have to say is IF YOU DON'T NEED THIS COURSE DO NOT TAKE IT! He knows that people who are in the course most likely need the credit that's why he's such an ass when it comes to tests and quizes. This is probably one of the worts courses I've ever taken and I would NEVER EVER take anything like this with him, let alone WITH HIM! Boring Class :

hmmm...as Prof. Bors would say himself "What's the probability that I will give him a good rating? ZEROOOOOOOOOO!!!" Seriously you guys...he seems like a nice guy but other than that...if you don't need this class...DON'T TAKE IT unless it's with another prof. Good luck to those who do take it with him

I was initially intimidated at taking this course, but Prof Bors made students feel more at ease by adding humour to some of his lectures.  The mid-term and tutorial quizzes can really boast your grades.  However, I advise that future students, *prepare* for the finals! Overall, a very effective professor!

He's funny, and i like going to stats class believe it or not. BUT... he is unclear ... because he tries to tie all concepts in while introducing new ones. Which is really a good thing but for some reason with him in this class it was an overload and made thigns superconfusing.

Had to drop my specialist in psych due to this class and his teaching methods. B07 was hard enough, I don't even want to fathom what c08 is. He really needs to clarify subject matter and not just magically expect us to understand. It's a large class, and not everyone has taken 1st and 2nd year calculus before taking the course.

I commend him, he LOVES stats... but very confusing and condescending. He seems to feel that students should know the material coming into class, though we only learn it during the course (supposedly). Stick to admin work.
unable to teach, only succeeded with ta's and study groups. slammed door in my face, should NOT be the head of the dept. if he is unable to communicate with students.
Good luck if this is a required course, you'll need it
horrible experience...only passed bc of study group who taught ourselves

i actually like him. he's very funny and very passionate about stats (!) but he is very unorganized in his lectures and notes. he needs someone to type up his lecture notes properly. he tries to make it easier for us to understand but he ends up making everything sound SO difficult.

This course totally screwed up my GPA- Bors is the nicest prof ever and tries his best to explain concepts during office hours...but lectures are HORRIBLE! I rarely understood what he was talking about in class because there was no organization and he makes even simple concepts hard to understand.

I read the book and understood the material. I went to class and the prof totally messed up what I already knew. Taking this class is a BAD IDEA unless it's a requirement. There's no organization of chapters and lectures. I finished the course and STILL don't understand what PSYB07 was about.

Very helpful, approachable, and knowledgeable but unable to explain simplest stats concepts in an understandable way. Lectures were extremely disorganized chaotic and irrelevant to course material. Do not listen to what he says in the lecture - just read the text. AVOID HIS COURSES! AT ALL COST!

The ppl who think this prof is bad just have a problem with statistics and would think any statistics/math prof horrible... If you've taken data in high school or calculus in uni, then you'll realize how good this prof really is.

Even when you know the material, after listening to him, he'll make you think you don't...that's when it's time to consult the book. Sigh. Just go to lecturse for "entertainment" value- i.e. find out what's on the exam. Besides that, i learned most of my stuff from tutorial or the text.But nice guy
worst prof I've ever had
worst prof. ever seen...and he is the head of the department????  HA!
course seems easy but he's making it sound hard..very UNORGANIZED in teaching..going back and forth between teaching materials..very hard to follow!!!!!!!!
Hate this course!! What is going on? Half course already passed and I still have clue what is this all about!
the prof makes the class harder than it really is and it is very hard to follow.  it is very unorganized in terms of the lecture notes corresponding to the lectures and to the text.
really confusing lectures, hard to follow, really helpful if you have questions though
The course context seems easy, but the professor is making it hard. I have no idea what he is talking about...talk too fast..and not clear at all.
No Comments
Amazing Prof.  Interesting lectures, good at answering questions.  Office hours availability often and helpful.  Answers e-mails quickly.
He is a good professor, but not the best one.  The jokes in the lectures are cool!
Tough to follow lectures...good at helping when you ask questions.
No Comments
He can be entertaining, but his lectures are disorganized and difficult to follow.
He is funnny... but seems very nice :) Certain words set him off (like he is eccentric): "now look at the GRAPH the INVERSE is UP!"
dont take his courses!!
Bors is a funny prof.
bors is bor(s)ing! and his lectures are unorganized.  the quizes are helpful though. avoid these classes if possible.
tough course, but willing to help all those who need it
Ok course, final all short answer no mc, so know your stuff!!
